In this speech, President Donald Trump addresses a gathering of America's builders, praising their skills and the importance of their work. He emphasizes his commitment to supporting American workers and protecting their jobs, promising to bring back jobs and the American Dream. Trump also discusses his plans for infrastructure development and reducing regulations that hinder construction projects. He highlights the achievements of his administration so far, such as the decrease in illegal immigration and the increase in consumer confidence. The President calls on all Americans to come together and participate in the rebuilding of the country. He ends the speech by invoking the Empire State Building as a symbol of American greatness and unity.